    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i've been watching the crows in my neighborhood for like two weeks now and something weird is happening. they aren't just making noise... they're actually signaling things. like yesterday there was this specific rhythmic clicking and they all moved south towards the park right before a massive thunderstorm hit out of nowhere. it's like they're communicating the pressure changes before they even happen. do u think they're actually using specific vocal cues to warn each other about the weather?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
